post_text:
Mark your calendars! The Calhan Bulldogs Booster Club will be hosting the 3rd Annual Chili Cook-Off/Silent Auction/Bake Sale event on Saturday, February 14th, 2015 during the basketball games! The event will start at 2:00 p.m. This is sure to be a lot of fun and there is something for everyone!
Please note, if you would like to enter the Chili Cook-Off, please have your chili to the school at 1:30 p.m. on February 14th. If you would like to provide an item for the Silent Auction, provide a baked good for the Bake Sale, bake a pie (as we sell pie by the slice), or volunteer for this event, please contact Terri Parks 719.237.4950.
We already have some great items for our Silent Auction to include, an overnight stay at a luxury hotel, tickets to a play, grocery store gift cards, hockey tickets, local nursery gift card, restaurant gift cards, family entertainment opportunities and more!
We are playing Limon that day, so if you have friends/family in Limon, please encourage them to come and participate!
Looking forward to seeing you all there! Go Bulldogs!

post_text: THIS SATURDAY, February 1, 2014 we have our Chili Cook Off, Silent Auction/Bake Sale! Please come out and support our basketball teams as they play ECA and enjoy a fun-filled day! Cash prizes will be awarded to first, second and third place in the Chili Cook Off. We have some great items for the Silent Auction and we have some of the BEST bakers in the Calhan area making baked goods for the Bake Sale and Pies to sell by the slice! We will also be serving a Chili Meal, hot dogs, nachos and slices of pie out of the concession stand. Please help us get the word out! If you can help out at this event, it would be greatly appreciated, as well. We will start setting up at 1:00 p.m. Mark your calendars as this is sure to be a fun time for all!!

post_text: This is just a reminder that our Community Pep Rally/Movie Night is THIS FRIDAY NIGHT, December 6th! Come out and meet the Winter Sportrs Athletes and enjoy a move and concessions following the Pep Rally. post_text:
Please plan to attend our next BIG event Friday, December 6, 2013! We are doing a Community Pep Rally/Movie Night!!! We want to introduce our Basketball and Wrestling Athletes to the Community! We will also have some of our new bulldog gear there as well! We will even be taking orders for your students' names and numbers to put on the back of your shirts if you want to personalize your Bulldog Gear! Lots of new items we can't wait to share with all of you!

Your movie selections to vote on this time are:

Coach Carter
Hoosiers
Blue Chips
He Got Game

We would love to hear from you, so please let us know which movie you would like to see. We will take suggestions for movies not on this list into consideration depending on the rating/content, etc.

We will also be serving concessions for this event so come out and have a great time! Help us to get the word out to the community, too!

post_text: We had a great homecoming weekend! Our Lady Bulldogs won in volleyball, the bonfire was awesome, the homecoming/alumni luncheon was a success, our Calhan Bulldogs Football team did great and never once did we forget the Ellis and O'Neill families. Many prayers to them both for all that they have been through and strength to keep going. Stay strong Jourdan and know that you have a whole lot of people pulling for you!

post_text: The school calendar says that there is a Booster Club Meeting Tuesday night, September 10th. We ARE NOT having a meeting on this day. We had to move our meeting up a week due to Homecoming being a little earlier this year. We will resume our regularly scheduled meeting schedule starting in October of having our meetings the 2nd Tuesday of the month, which will be October 8th for next month. Sorry for any confusion that this has caused.

As for setup on the day of the event, which is this Saturday, we will be getting things ready to go at 8:30 in the morning. We will be serving food beginning immediately after the parade around 11 a.m. So if you would be able to help with any or all of these times it would be greatly appreciated!
